If you move out of state with a California registered vehicle, let DMV know by changing your address at dmv.ca.gov/address-change. If you get a renewal notice but left California before registration expired, complete the back of the renewal notice or a Statement of Facts {{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}REG 256 {{/ifCond}} form with the date the vehicle left California, the date the vehicle was registered out of state, and the state's name where it is now registered. 
{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}
