For a REAL ID driver's license or identification card, federal regulations require 1 identity document and 2 residency documents, and your social security number.
Your identity document must be an original or certified copy. Residency documents must match both the name and address in your application. View the Easy as 1-2-3 REAL ID Document List or the REAL ID Checklist for more documents.
{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}
* [Easy as 1-2-3 REAL ID Document List](https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/uploads/2020/06/dl1010E.pdf)
* [REAL ID Checklist](https://realid.dmv.ca.gov/your-real-id-checklist/)
{{/ifCond}}

A partir del 1st de enero de 2020, una licencia de conducir en poder de un miembro del Servicio Exterior de los Estados Unidos o su cónyuge, permanece válida durante todo el período en que el miembro o cónyuge permanece fuera del estado en servicio activo y 30 días después de que regrese al estado, siempre y cuando la licencia de conducir no sea suspendida, cancelada o revocada.
{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}
[Veterans and Active Duty Military](https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/driver-education-and-safety/special-interest-driver-guides/veterans-and-active-duty-military/)
{{/ifCond}}

Renewal notices are mailed to the address on record 120 days prior to the expiration date on your driver's license/ID card and will state if you are eligible to renew online, by mail. *No address updates are allowed during the renewal process.
{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}
* [Driver's License or ID Card Renewal](https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/driver-licenses-identification-cards/renew-your-driver-license-dl-or-identification-card-id/)
