You must submit a Notice of Transfer and Release of Liability form within 5 calendar days from the date you sell or transfer your vehicle. Keep a copy for your records. 
Note: Submitting a Notice of Transfer and Release of Liability to DMV is not a transfer of ownership. The vehicle record is not transferred out of your name until DMV receives a completed application for transfer of ownership and payment of appropriate fees from the new owner.

{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}
* [Notice of Transfer and Release of Liability Online](https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/vehicle-registration/titles/title-transfers-and-changes/notice-of-transfer-and-release-of-liability-nrl/)
* [Notice of Transfer and Release of Liability by Mail](https://www.dmv.ca.gov/portal/dmv/detail/forms/reg/reg138)
{{/ifCond}}

Nonresident Active Duty Military personnel stationed in California are exempt from paying the vehicle license fee or V,L,F, on an owned or leased vehicle registered under their name in California. To obtain the V,L,F, exemption, military personnel must complete a Nonresident Military Exemption Statement 
