To add a firefighter endorsement to your driver's license, you must complete an application, pay the fee, and submit an original firefighter employment and training verification signed by the fire chief on fire department letterhead. You must also submit certification of employment as a firefighter, certification of completion of fire equipment operator training, and a Health Questionnaire {{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'miles'}}DL546{{/ifCond}}{{#ifCond SessionAttributes.QNAClientFilter '===' 'ivr'}}D,L,546{{/ifCond}} form.

